{{Unsourced|date=February 2015}} {{YearInIrelandNav | 1651 }} Events from the year '''1651 in Ireland'''. ==Events== *January – [[Edmund Ludlow]] lands in Ireland as lieutenant-general of horse and second-in-command to [[Henry Ireton]]. *June – restart of the [[Siege of Limerick (1650–1651)|Siege of Limerick]] by English Parliamentarian troops under Ireton. *July – [[Battle of Knocknaclashy]]. Irish force trying to relieve Limerick is routed. *August – start of the [[Siege of Galway]]: an English Parliamentarian army under [[Charles Coote, 1st Earl of Mountrath|Charles Coote]] blockades the city. *[[October 27]] – [[Siege of Limerick (1650–1651)|Siege of Limerick]]: [[Hugh Dubh O'Neill]] surrenders Limerick after part of the English Royalist garrison mutinies. The soldiers are permitted to march unarmed to [[Galway]] but some leaders are executed. *[[November 26]] – [[Henry Ireton]] dies of fever and is succeeded in command by [[Edmund Ludlow]].
==Births==
{{Empty section|date=February 2013}}
==Deaths== *[[October 31]] – executions by the English Parliamentarians after the surrender of Limerick: **[[Terence Albert O'Brien]], [[Roman Catholic]] [[Bishop of Emly]] (b.[[1600 in Ireland|1600]]) **Dominic Fanning, Alderman. *[[November 26]] – [[Henry Ireton]] , English Parliamentarian commander (b.[[1611 in Ireland|1611]]) *[[Richard Butler, 3rd Viscount Mountgarret]], landowner and former Irish Confederate military commander (b.[[1578 in Ireland|1578]])
