{{Infobox language |name=Bwela |nativename= |region= |states=[[Democratic Republic of Congo]] |speakers=8,400 |date=2002 |ref=e18 |familycolor=Niger-Congo |fam2=[[Atlantic–Congo languages|Atlantic–Congo]] |fam3=[[Benue–Congo languages|Benue–Congo]] |fam4=[[Bantoid languages|Bantoid]] |fam5=[[Bantu languages|Bantu]] |fam6=[[Buja–Ngombe languages|Buja–Ngombe]]? |iso3=bwl |guthrie=C.42 |glotto=bwel1238 |glottorefname=Bwela }}
'''Bwela''', or ''Lingi'', is a poorly known Congolese [[Bantu language]] of uncertain affiliation (though listed as [[Guthrie classification of Bantu languages#Zone C|Zone C.40]] by Guthrie). It may be close to [[Motembo language|Tembo]].<ref name="Glottolog" />
