{{about|the 1968  Sanremo Festival entrant|the 1991 Eurovision entrant|Canzone per te}}

'''"Canzone per te"''' ("A song for you"), written by Italian composer [[Sergio Endrigo]] and sung by Brazilian singer [[Roberto Carlos (singer)|Roberto Carlos]], was the [[Italy|Italian]] entrant to and winner of [[Sanremo Music Festival 1968|the 1968 edition]] of the [[Sanremo Music Festival]]. 

On the night of the contest, held in [[Sanremo]], [[Italy]], the song was performed by both Endrigo and Carlos.

==Recordings==

[[Sergio Franchi]] recorded an English-language version of this song ("I Wrote a Song For You") on his 1968 RCA Victor album ''Wine and Song.''<ref>http://www.discogs.com Sergio Franchi</ref>

