===Union Jack===
{{See also|British ensign|Flags of the British Empire}}
[[File:Flag of Fiji.svg|thumb|100px|National flag of Fiji]]
[[File:Flag of Bermuda.svg|thumb|100px|flag of Bermuda]]
[[File:Flag of the United Kingdom.svg|thumb|100px|flag of the United Kingdom]]
[[File:Flag_of_South_Africa_(1928-1994).svg|thumb|100px|flag of South Africa (1928–1994]]
[[File:Canadian Red Ensign (1957-1965).svg|thumb|100px|National flag of Canada 1957–1965]]

*{{flagof|Australia}}
*{{flagof|Australia|1901}} (1901–1903)
*{{flagof|Australia|1903}} (1903–1908)
*{{flagof|Bermuda|1910}} (1910–1999)
*{{flagof|Canada|1868}} (1868–1921)
*{{flagof|Canada|1921}} (1921–1957)
*{{flagof|Canada|1957}} (1957–1965) 
*{{flagof|Kingdom of Great Britain|Great Britain|1707}} (1707–1801)
*{{flagof|Fiji}}
*{{flagof|New Zealand}}
*{{flagof|Newfoundland|1907}} (1907–1949)
*{{flagof|South Africa|1928|section=1928–94 flag}} (1928–1994)
*{{flagof|South Africa|1910}} (1910–1928)
*{{flagof|Tuvalu}}
*{{flagof|Tuvalu|1976}} (1976–1978)
*{{flagof|Tuvalu|1978}} (1978–1996)
*{{flagof|the=yes|United Kingdom of Great Britain and Northern Ireland}}
*{{flagof|the=yes|United States|1776}} (1775–1777)

Additionally, the Union Jack features in many territorial and sub-national flags. These are often [[Red Ensign]]s (e.g., {{flagof|Bermuda}}) or [[Blue Ensign]]s (e.g., {{flagof|New South Wales}} and {{flagof|Anguilla}}). A small number have backgrounds of other colours (e.g. {{flagof|British Antarctic Territory}} and {{flagof|Niue}}) or a unique pattern in the field (e.g. {{flagof|British Indian Ocean Territory}} and {{flagof|Hawaii}}). A small number put the Union Jack somewhere other than the canton (e.g. {{flagof|British Columbia}}). Unofficial flags, such as {{flagof|Ross Dependency|unofficial}} also use it.
{{clear}}

