{{refimprove|date=June 2015}} {{Infobox olive cultivar | name = Meslalla | image = | color = Green | also_called = Cracked green olive | origin = Morocco | regions = | hazards = | use = Oil and pickling | oil_content = High | fertility = Self-sterile | growth = Spreading | leaf = Elliptic-lanceolate | weight = Medium | shape = Ovoid | symmetry = Slightly asymmetrical }}
'''Meslalla''' (cracked green olive,<ref>{{cite web|title=OLIVES MESLALLA|url=http://www.authenticmaroc.com/en/olives/olives-meslalla/S17_2C17|publisher=authenticmaroc.com|accessdate=24 January 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Moroccan Temrika Meslalla — Garlic Beef with Cracked Green Olives|url=http://kalisasorexi.com/2011/02/moroccan-temrika-meslalla-garlic-beef-with-cracked-green-olives/|publisher=kalisasorexi.com|accessdate=24 January 2017|date=13 February 2011}}</ref>) is a Moroccan green [[olive]] cultivar used for olive oil production, pickled in [[garlic]] and hot peppers. It is also used in [[tagine]]s.<ref>[http://www.jmaterenvironsci.com/Document/vol4/vol4_N6/126-JMES-482-2013-Gharby.pdf Chemical Characterization and oxidative stability of two monovarietal virgin olive oils (Moroccan Picholine and Arbequina) grown in Morocco].</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=The Sésame Des Saveurs|url=http://sesamedessaveurs.over-blog.com/article-olives-meslalla-marinees-112873428.html|publisher=sesamedessaveurs.over-blog.com|accessdate=24 January 2017|language=French|date=22 December 2014}}</ref>
